<p><strong>Tree removal cost in Concord NC</strong> ranges from $250 to $2,500 for most residential jobs. The final number depends on tree size, location on your property, and how complex the job is to execute safely.</p>

<h2>Tree Removal Prices in Concord by Size</h2>

<p>Tree height is the primary factor driving your cost. A shorter tree takes less time, fewer cuts, and lighter equipment. Taller trees require rigging, sectional removal, and often a dedicated crane or bucket truck.</p>

<p>Here is what most <a href="/concord/">Concord homeowners</a> pay based on tree height:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Under 25 feet</strong> (ornamental trees, small pines): $150 to $500</li>
  <li><strong>25 to 50 feet</strong> (average yard trees, dogwoods, smaller oaks): $500 to $1,000</li>
  <li><strong>50 to 75 feet</strong> (mature oaks, large pines, sweetgums): $1,000 to $1,800</li>
  <li><strong>Over 75 feet</strong> (very large hardwoods, old growth): $1,500 to $3,000+</li>
</ul>

<p>Concord sits in the Piedmont region where loblolly pines, sweetgums, and red oaks are common. Most residential removals in Cabarrus County fall in the $400 to $1,200 range because the average yard tree here runs 30 to 60 feet tall.</p>

<h2>What Else Affects the Price</h2>

<p>Height is not the only factor. Several conditions can push the cost higher or bring it down.</p>

<p><strong>Proximity to structures.</strong> A tree leaning over your roof, near a fence, or tangled in power lines requires more cautious rigging. Crews may need to remove the tree in small sections instead of felling it in one direction. Expect a 20 to 40 percent increase in price for trees near homes or utility lines.</p>

<p><strong>Trunk diameter.</strong> Two 40-foot trees can have very different trunk sizes. A 30-inch diameter trunk takes significantly more cutting time and produces more wood to haul than a 12-inch trunk.</p>

<p><strong>Access to the tree.</strong> If your crew can drive equipment right up to the tree, the job goes faster. If the tree is in a fenced backyard, behind a shed, or on a steep slope, the crew has to carry everything by hand. Limited access adds time and cost.</p>

<p><strong>Number of trees.</strong> Most companies offer a discount when you remove multiple trees at once. The crew and equipment are already on-site, so the per-tree cost drops. If you have three or four trees to take down, ask about a package price.</p>

<p><strong>Deadwood or storm damage.</strong> Dead trees are unpredictable. Branches can snap during removal, and the trunk may be hollow or structurally compromised. <a href="/emergency-tree-service/">Emergency tree removal</a> after storms can cost more due to urgency and hazardous conditions, with an average around $843 in the Concord area.</p>

<p>Every property is different. The fastest way to get an accurate price is a free on-site estimate.</p>

