<h2>Tree Removal Cost FAQs</h2>

<h3>What is the average tree removal cost in Concord NC?</h3>
<p>Most homeowners pay between $400 and $1,200 for a standard residential tree removal. The average across the Concord area is around $564. Smaller trees under 25 feet cost as little as $150, while large hardwoods over 75 feet can run $2,500 or more.</p>

<h3>Does the price include stump removal?</h3>
<p>Usually not. Stump grinding is a separate service that costs $100 to $400 in Concord. Ask for a bundled quote when scheduling your tree removal to save on the combined cost.</p>

<h3>Is emergency tree removal more expensive?</h3>
<p>Yes. <a href="/emergency-tree-service/">Emergency tree removal</a> averages around $843 in Concord due to urgency, after-hours response, and hazardous conditions from storm damage.</p>

<h3>When is the cheapest time to remove a tree?</h3>
<p>Late fall through winter (November to February) is typically the slowest season for tree services. Many companies offer lower rates during this period because demand is lower.</p>

